field.value:
I've had a few exceptions in SelfValidationContributor.Initialize which seems to be caused by the same type being added several times to the hashtable methodsPerType. As far as I can see, it looks like there is not sufficient locking being made in the caller AbstractValidationContributor.IsValid.

The code in IsValid looks like this:

if (!initialized.Contains(instanceType))
{
    Initialize(instanceType);
    initialized.Add(instanceType);
}

and that is not sufficient to guarantee that two threads will never enter initialize.Add with the same instanceType.

I'm using ver. 5332 of the trunk.
